## Description {#details}

Result of a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/liverange">LiveRange</a> query.

This class hides the implementation details of live ranges, and it should be used as the primary interface for examining live ranges around instructions.

Definition at line 90 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/liveinterval-h">LiveInterval.h</a>.

## Public Member Functions

### endPoint() {#accf3c068536d27391a38eaec0db05eec}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="SlotIndex llvm::LiveQueryResult::endPoint () const"
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Return the end point of the last live range segment to interact with the instruction, if any.

The end point is an invalid <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/slotindex">SlotIndex</a> only if the live range doesn&#39;t intersect the instruction at all.

The end point may be at or past the end of the instruction&#39;s basic block. That means the value was live out of the block.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/liveinterval-h/#l00147">147</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/liveinterval-h">LiveInterval.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### isKill() {#af155aeaffc7607f4f27ab4cfcbb39a64}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="bool llvm::LiveQueryResult::isKill () const"
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Return true if the live-in value is killed by this instruction.

This means that either the live range ends at the instruction, or it changes value.

This includes dead defs, it is the value created by the instruction&#39;s def operands.

### valueIn() {#a527e4a21e13a8455c75eb0d811701066}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>VNInfo &#42; llvm::LiveQueryResult::valueIn () const</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Return the value that is live-in to the instruction.

This is the value that will be read by the instruction&#39;s use operands. Return NULL if no value is live-in.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/liveinterval-h/#l00105">105</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/liveinterval-h">LiveInterval.h</a>.

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>VNInfo &#42; llvm::LiveQueryResult::valueOut () const</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Return the value leaving the instruction, if any.

This can be a live-through value, or a live def. A dead def returns NULL.
